  <prompt>
    Replace the BODY of `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/CreateRecordWizard/steps/SendEmailStep.tsx` with the canonical `<SendEmailStep />` wrapper (built in Wave 1 task 021). This single file change migrates CreateProject, CreateEvent, CreateTodo, and CreateWorkAssignment wizards in one shot — per empirical scan (CLAUDE.md DELTA #12), all four wizards consume this shared file from the canonical source path.

    The exported component must preserve its current public prop API so callers do not need to change. Internally it now mounts `<SendEmailStep />` from the canonical wrapper, passing through the wizard-context-shaped props (recipients, subject, body, associatedTo, onSent, etc.) translated to the canonical wrapper's prop API.

    EMPIRICAL NOTE: Per CLAUDE.md DELTA #9, the spec's FR-16 phrasing "5 wizards migrate" overstates the per-file count. Only 2 files contain the per-wizard SendEmailStep: this shared file (consumed by Project/Event/Todo/WorkAssignment) AND `CreateMatterWizard/SendEmailStep.tsx` (task 072). LegalWorkspace's Project/Event/Todo/WorkAssignment dirs have NO SendEmailStep file. Wave 5 scope is correspondingly smaller than FR-16/FR-25 phrasing implied.

    NOTE per Owner Clarification: All Wave 5 changes ship as a single PR (task 076). Do not push as standalone.
  </prompt>

